# Git Commit Identity (required)

Every commit in this repository must use:

- **Author**: `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>`
- **Committer**: `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>`

## Forbidden

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor/agent co-author trailer
- Any other `Co-authored-by` line unless the user explicitly asks for co-authorship
- `suherman@qantas.com.au` or `suherman@qantas` anywhere in author, committer, or message
- Running `git config` to change user.name or user.email

## When creating commits

1. Install hooks once per clone if missing: `bash scripts/install-git-hooks.sh`
2. Prefer `bash scripts/git-commit.sh "$(cat <<'EOF' ... EOF)"` or explicit env vars:

```bash
GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Iman Suherman" \
GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="iman.suherman@gmail.com" \
git commit --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Commit message here.

EOF
)"
```

3. After **every** commit you create, run:

```bash
bash scripts/rewrite-commit-identity.sh
git log -1 --format='%an <%ae>%n%ce%n%B'
```

4. Confirm the output shows only `iman.suherman@gmail.com` and no `Co-authored-by` lines.

## Enforcement

Git hooks in `scripts/git-hooks/` (installed by `scripts/install-git-hooks.sh`):

- **prepare-commit-msg** — strips Cursor co-author before commit completes
- **commit-msg** — rejects Cursor co-author and qantas email references
- **post-commit** — auto-runs `scripts/rewrite-commit-identity.sh` if identity or message is wrong

Do not skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless the user explicitly requests it.

## History cleanup

```bash
bash scripts/install-git-hooks.sh
bash scripts/rewrite-commit-identity.sh   # latest commit only
```

For full history:

```bash
git filter-repo --force --env-filter '...' --message-callback '...'
```

Only rewrite and force-push when the user explicitly asks.
